AT
AT=OA\left(2\sin\dfrac{\pi}{7}\right)
2\cos\dfrac{2\pi}{7}=2-\left(2\sin\dfrac{\pi}{7}\right)^2
x=2\cos\dfrac{2\pi}{7}
x^3+x^2-2x-1=0
2\sin\dfrac{\pi}{7}
(2-x^2)^3+(2-x^2)^2-2(2-x^2)-1=0
-2\sin\dfrac{\pi}{7}
\pm 2\sin\dfrac{2\pi}{7}
\pm 2\sin\dfrac{3\pi}{7}
\left(x^3+\sqrt 7\left(x^2-1\right)\right)\left(x^3-\sqrt 7\left(x^2-1\right)\right)=0
2\sin\dfrac{\pi}{7}
-2\sin\dfrac{2\pi}{7}
-2\sin\dfrac{3\pi}{7}
\left(\frac1{x}\right)^3-\frac1{x}=\frac1{\sqrt 7}
\dfrac1{x}=\dfrac2{\sqrt 3}\cos\,\psi
\cos\,3\psi=\sqrt{\dfrac{27}{28}}
\psi=\frac13\arccos\sqrt{\frac{27}{28}}=\frac13\arctan\frac1{3\sqrt 3}
2\sin\frac{\pi}{7}\cos\,\psi=\frac{\sqrt 3}{2}
\angle NAP=\arctan\dfrac1{3\sqrt 3}
\angle NAT=\psi
AT\cos\,\psi=AN=\dfrac{\sqrt 3}{2}OA
AT=OA\left(2\sin\dfrac{\pi}{7}\right)
